Questions Javascript intro

1. Explain the difference between the == operator and the === operator.

The == operator compares two values, and considers values to be equal when the value of  both is equal to the other.
The === operator compares two values, but considers values to be equal only when the values are exactly equal to each other.

2. Explain what a closure is. (Note that JavaScript programs use closures very often)

Closure is a function that calls a local variable that is set in a near scope.
Calling it from near the scope enables not having to worry about the lifetime of the binding and to use function values in creative ways.

3. Explain what higher order functions are.

Functions that operate on other functions, either by taking them as arguments or by returning them.

4. Explain what a query selector is and give an example line of JavaScript that uses a query selector.

A query selector is used to select elements from HTML. It returns the first element that matches a specified CSS selector in the document. 
The query selector all function selects all elements taht match the specific CSS selector.
